race.description: Merry Christmas From The Rjc (Bm55) Handicap
race.comment: JAY BEE ELL (4) was back to his best last start when closing strongly to arrive just in time to score by a bob here. Boasts a strong record here and can keep the momentum rolling. HE'S THE ONE (3) hasn't won for a long time but is knocking on the door. Has peaks that measure up but will likely be coming from the back. Watch for him charging late. SMASHING ROSIE (6) made light work of her rivals here last start. Backs up quickly and while she's yet to have success over this journey, she will appreciate the added trip jumping from the wide alley. 3kg claimer gets her in well. Is another one to watch for late in the piece. EL FORTRESS (2) has returned in good order this prep and should be hitting his straps on the quick back-up. Is another that's drawn poorly though so will need some luck.
